  "title": "Optics Engineer (Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Develop and optimize optical systems for lighting/illumination in semiconductor manufacturing equipment.</li>\n  <li>Perform optical simulations, ray tracing, and tolerance analysis to enhance system performance.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to prototype, test, and validate optical designs.</li>\n  <li>Identify and resolve optical performance issues to improve efficiency and accuracy in manufacturing processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree and above</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience in <strong>optics design/optical systems.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of <strong>optical and mechanical design</strong>, with hands-on experience in <strong>optical performance testing</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in <strong>Zemax</strong>, <strong>chromatic aberrations, MTF, and precision measurement techniques</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to<strong> hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
